funcs.name: dom_document_validate
funcs.desc:
Validates the document based on its DTD.

You can also use the validateOnParse property of DOMDocument to make a DTD validation.

return.desc: Returns TRUE on success or FALSE on failure. If the document have no DTD attached, this method will return FALSE.
Returns the number of XIncludes in the document, -1 if some processing failed, or FALSE if there were no substitutions.

args.name: obj
args.desc: libxml parameters. Available since PHP 5.1.0 and Libxml 2.6.7.

funcs.name: dom_node_normalize
funcs.desc: Normalizes the node.

return.desc: No value is returned.

funcs.name: dom_nodelist_item
funcs.desc:
Retrieves a node specified by index within the DOMNodeList object. Tip

If you need to know the number of nodes in the collection, use the length property of the DOMNodeList object.

return.desc: The node at the indexth position in the DOMNodeList, or NULL if that is not a valid index.

args.name: obj
args.desc: Index of the node into the collection.

funcs.name: dom_namednodemap_item
funcs.desc: Retrieves a node specified by index within the DOMNamedNodeMap object.

return.desc: The node at the indexth position in the map, or NULL if that is not a valid index (greater than or equal to the number of nodes in this map).

args.name: obj
args.desc: Index into this map.

funcs.name: dom_xpath_query
funcs.desc: Executes the given XPath expression.

return.desc: Returns a DOMNodeList containing all nodes matching the given XPath expression. Any expression which do not return nodes will return an empty DOMNodeList.

args.name: obj
args.desc: The XPath expression to execute.

args.name: expr
args.desc: The optional contextnode can be specified for doing relative XPath queries. By default, the queries are relative to the root element.

funcs.name: dom_xpath_evaluate
funcs.desc: Executes the given XPath expression and returns a typed result if possible.

return.desc: Returns a typed result if possible or a DOMNodeList containing all nodes matching the given XPath expression.

args.name: obj
args.desc: The XPath expression to execute.

args.name: expr
args.desc: The optional contextnode can be specified for doing relative XPath queries. By default, the queries are relative to the root element.

args.desc: The SimpleXMLElement node.

args.name: node
args.desc: The removed child.

funcs.name: replaceChild
funcs.desc: This function replaces the child oldnode with the passed new node. If the new node is already a child it will not be added a second time. If the replacement succeeds the old node is returned.

return.desc: The old node or FALSE if an error occur.

args.name: newchildobj
args.desc: The new node. It must be a member of the target document, i.e. created by one of the DOMDocument->createXXX() methods or imported in the document by DOMDocument::importNode.

args.name: oldchildobj
args.desc: The old node.

classes.name: DOMAttr
classes.desc: DOMAttr represents an attribute in the DOMElement object.

funcs.name: isId
funcs.desc:
This function checks if the attribute is a defined ID.

According to the DOM standard this requires a DTD which defines the attribute ID to be of type ID. You need to validate your document with DOMDocument::validate or DOMDocument::validateOnParse before using this function.

return.desc: Returns TRUE on success or FALSE on failure.

classes.name: DOMCharacterData
classes.desc: Represents nodes with character data. No nodes directly correspond to this class, but other nodes do inherit from it.

funcs.name: appendData
funcs.desc: Append the string data to the end of the character data of the node.

return.desc: No value is returned.

args.name: arg
args.desc: The string to append.

funcs.name: deleteData
funcs.desc: Deletes count characters starting from position offset.

return.desc: No value is returned.

args.name: offset
args.desc: The offset from which to start removing.

args.name: count
args.desc: The number of characters to delete. If the sum of offset and count exceeds the length, then all characters to the end of the data are deleted.

funcs.name: insertData
funcs.desc: Inserts string data at position offset.

return.desc: No value is returned.

args.name: offset
args.desc: The character offset at which to insert.

args.name: data
args.desc: The string to insert.

funcs.name: replaceData
funcs.desc: Replace count characters starting from position offset with data.

return.desc: No value is returned.

args.name: offset
args.desc: The offset from which to start replacing.

args.name: count
args.desc: The number of characters to replace. If the sum of offset and count exceeds the length, then all characters to the end of the data are replaced.

args.name: data
args.desc: The string with which the range must be replaced.

funcs.name: substringData
funcs.desc: Returns the specified substring.

return.desc: The specified substring. If the sum of offset and count exceeds the length, then all 16-bit units to the end of the data are returned.

args.name: offset
args.desc: Start offset of substring to extract.

args.name: count
args.desc: The number of characters to extract.

classes.name: DOMComment
classes.desc: Represents comment nodes, characters delimited by <!-- and -->.

classes.name: DOMText
classes.desc: The DOMText class inherits from DOMCharacterData and represents the textual content of a DOMElement or DOMAttr.

funcs.name: isWhitespaceInElementContent
funcs.desc: Indicates whether this text node contains whitespace. The text node is determined to contain whitespace in element content during the load of the document.

return.desc: Returns TRUE on success or FALSE on failure.

funcs.name: splitText
funcs.desc:
Breaks this node into two nodes at the specified offset, keeping both in the tree as siblings.

After being split, this node will contain all the content up to the offset. If the original node had a parent node, the new node is inserted as the next sibling of the original node. When the offset is equal to the length of this node, the new node has no data.

return.desc: The new node of the same type, which contains all the content at and after the offset.

args.name: offset
args.desc: The offset at which to split, starting from 0.

funcs.name: getElementById
funcs.desc:
This function is similar to DOMDocument::getElementsByTagName but searches for an element with a given id.

For this function to work, you will need either to set some ID attributes with DOMElement::setIdAttribute or a DTD which defines an attribute to be of type ID. In the later case, you will need to validate your document with DOMDocument::validate or DOMDocument->validateOnParse before using this function.

return.desc: Returns the DOMElement or NULL if the element is not found.

args.name: elementid
args.desc: The unique id value for an element.

funcs.name: getElementsByTagName
funcs.desc: This function returns a new instance of class DOMNodeList containing the elements with a given tag name.

return.desc: A new DOMNodeList object containing all the matched elements.

args.name: name
args.desc: The name of the tag to match on. The special value * matches all tags.

funcs.name: getElementsByTagNameNS
funcs.desc: Returns a DOMNodeList of all elements with a given local name and a namespace URI.

return.desc: A new DOMNodeList object containing all the matched elements.

args.name: namespaceuri
args.desc: The namespace URI of the elements to match on. The special value * matches all namespaces.

args.name: localname
args.desc: The local name of the elements to match on. The special value * matches all local names.

funcs.name: importNode
funcs.desc: This function returns a copy of the node to import and associates it with the current document.

return.desc: The copied node or FALSE, if it cannot be copied.

args.name: importednode
args.desc: The node to import.

args.name: deep
args.desc:
If set to TRUE, this method will recursively import the subtree under the importedNode.

To copy the nodes attributes deep needs to be set to TRUE

funcs.name: load
funcs.desc: Loads an XML document from a file. Warning Unix style paths with forward slashes can cause significant performance degradation on Windows systems; be sure to call realpath() in such a case.

return.desc: Returns TRUE on success or FALSE on failure. If called statically, returns a DOMDocument and issues E_STRICT warning.

args.name: filename
args.desc: The path to the XML document.

args.name: options
args.desc: Bitwise OR of the libxml option constants.

funcs.name: loadHTML
funcs.desc: The function parses the HTML contained in the string source. Unlike loading XML, HTML does not have to be well-formed to load. This function may also be called statically to load and create a DOMDocument object. The static invocation may be used when no DOMDocument properties need to be set prior to loading.

return.desc: Returns TRUE on success or FALSE on failure. If called statically, returns a DOMDocument and issues E_STRICT warning.

args.name: source
args.desc: The HTML string.

funcs.name: loadHTMLFile
funcs.desc:
The function parses the HTML document in the file named filename. Unlike loading XML, HTML does not have to be well-formed to load.

Though not recommended, this function may also be called statically to load and create a DOMDocument object. The static invocation may be used when no DOMDocument properties need to be set prior to loading. However, doing so will result an in E_STRICT error being generated.

return.desc: Returns TRUE on success or FALSE on failure. If called statically, returns a DOMDocument and issues E_STRICT warning.

args.name: filename
args.desc: The path to the HTML file.

funcs.name: loadXML
funcs.desc:
Loads an XML document from a string.

This method may also be called statically to load and create a DOMDocument object. The static invocation may be used when no DOMDocument properties need to be set prior to loading.

return.desc: Returns TRUE on success or FALSE on failure. If called statically, returns a DOMDocument and issues E_STRICT warning.

args.name: source
args.desc: The string containing the XML.

args.name: options
args.desc: Bitwise OR of the libxml option constants.

funcs.name: normalizeDocument
funcs.desc: This method acts as if you saved and then loaded the document, putting the document in a "normal" form.

return.desc: No value is returned.

funcs.name: registerNodeClass
funcs.desc:
This method allows you to register your own extended DOM class to be used afterward by the PHP DOM extension.

This method is not part of the DOM standard.

return.desc: Returns TRUE on success or FALSE on failure.

args.name: baseclass
args.desc: The DOM class that you want to extend. You can find a list of these classes in the chapter introduction.

args.name: extendedclass
args.desc: Your extended class name. If NULL is provided, any previously registered class extending baseclass will be removed.

return.desc: Returns TRUE on success or FALSE on failure.

args.name: filename
args.desc: The RNG file.

return.desc: Returns TRUE on success or FALSE on failure.

args.name: source
args.desc: A string containing the RNG schema.

funcs.name: appendXML
funcs.desc:
Appends raw XML data to a DOMDocumentFragment.

This method is not part of the DOM standard. It was created as a simpler approach for appending an XML DocumentFragment in a DOMDocument.

If you want to stick to the standards, you will have to create a temporary DOMDocument with a dummy root and then loop through the child nodes of the root of your XML data to append them.

return.desc: Returns TRUE on success or FALSE on failure.

args.name: data
args.desc: XML to append.

funcs.name: evaluate
funcs.desc: Executes the given XPath expression and returns a typed result if possible.

return.desc: Returns a typed result if possible or a DOMNodeList containing all nodes matching the given XPath expression.

args.name: expr
args.desc: The XPath expression to execute.

args.name: context
args.desc: The optional contextnode can be specified for doing relative XPath queries. By default, the queries are relative to the root element.

funcs.name: query
funcs.desc: Executes the given XPath expression.

return.desc: Returns a DOMNodeList containing all nodes matching the given XPath expression. Any expression which do not return nodes will return an empty DOMNodeList.

args.name: expr

funcs.desc: This method enables the ability to use PHP functions within XPath expressions.

args.name: funcs
args.desc:
Use this parameter to only allow certain functions to be called from XPath.

This parameter can be either a string (a function name) or an array of function names.
